# Goozi Project Template

This directory is a project template. Use `create-project.sh` (Linux/Mac) or `create-project.bat` (Windows) to generate a new project from this template.

## Usage

### Linux/Mac
```bash
./create-project.sh [project-name] [target-directory]
```

### Windows
```cmd
create-project.bat [project-name] [target-directory]
```

## What gets replaced

The script will replace the following placeholders:
- `goozi` → project name (lowercase)
- `Goozi` → project name (capitalized)
- `GOOZI` → project name (uppercase)
- `goozi_db` → project_name_db
- `goozi-network` → project-name-network
- `goozi-postgres` → project-name-postgres
- `goozi-backend` → project-name-backend
- `goozi-web` → project-name-web
- `goozi-cms` → project-name-cms

## Excluded files/directories

The following are excluded when copying:
- `node_modules/`
- `.git/`
- `.env` and `.env.*`
- `dist/` and `build/`
- `uploads/*`
- `*.log`
- `.cache/`
- `coverage/`
- `.nyc_output/`
